\begin{center}
\textbf{{\huge 7.Drawbacks of this experiment}}
\end{center}
\vspace{5 mm}
There are several variables on which the experiment depends.But we do not have enough equipment to control
every such variables.So we only took those variables in consideration which we can control.The drawbacks are as follows:
\begin{itemize}
\item Temperature plays an important role in varying the elasticity of the rubber band resulting different distance in same extension of the rubber band.This can  be controlled by performing the experiment in a temperature constant room.We were not able to do that due to limited resources.
\item Air resistance also happens to affect this experiment.It an be controlled by performing this in a vacuum room.But we were not able to do that due to limited resources.
\item We used a chair to support the scale used to launch the rubber bands.And we ourselves release the rubber band by releasing hand over scale .This may not give full accuracy since our extension strength of band may change.Though it can be corrected by using a mechanical object like a robot.
\end{itemize}



